## A Query Language for APIs
Unlike REST (where you hit multiple URLs for different data), GraphQL exposes a single endpoint (e.g., `/graphql`).

- The **Client** dictates exactly what data it wants.
- Prevents **Over-fetching** (getting too much data) and **Under-fetching** (needing to make 5 requests to get everything).

```graphql
query {
  user(id: 1) {
    name
    posts {
      title
    }
  }
}
```

